Checkpoint/SavedModel compatibility utilities; TF-dependent export/import behind features.
Sparse optimizer configs and step rules used by embedding backends.
Generated protobuf types and gRPC stubs shared across crates.

cliConfigEnv.behavior: Preserve CLI/env precedence: (1) explicit API params/RunConfig fields, (2) absl.flags, (3) environment variables (e.g. TF_CONFIG, CLOUDNATIVE_INET_ADDR/YARN_INET_ADDR, PRIMUS_AM_RPC_*), (4) implicit defaults. Maintain existing flag names for compatibility where feasible. Rust should accept a structured config (JSON/YAML) and optionally mirror key flags for drop-in job tooling.
compatibilityChecks: Training job can start with existing TF_CONFIG/cluster discovery inputs without requiring code changes (when tf-runtime feature enabled).
RunConfig/RunnerConfig serialization round-trips (Python dataclass_json <-> Rust serde) with identical defaults and override semantics.
Feature list and parser context options resolve deterministically for the same flags/env (no timestamps/random ordering).

disk: Any custom protos or JSON configs
compatibilityChecks: Rust can read existing monolith_checkpoint file and MonolithCheckpointState text proto.
Rust can parse and emit the same protobuf config messages used by embedding hash tables and optimizers.
When tf-runtime feature is enabled, exported SavedModel directory layout matches Python exporter (entry/ps_*/dense_* subdirs, assets, signatures).

crossLangParity.strategy: Use Python as oracle: generate fixtures and expected outputs; Rust loads raw fixtures and compares canonicalized outputs. Canonicalization rules: sorted map keys, stable ordering of feature slots, explicit dtype tags, and stable float formatting. TF-dependent parity is behind cargo features; default Rust tests must not require TF runtime.

goldens.description: Decode a tiny Instance protobuf stream into sparse fid lists + dense fields; compare canonical JSON.
Serialize optimizer/initializer/compressor configs to embedding_hash_table protos and compare bytes+JSON.
Parse monolith_checkpoint text proto and validate exemption path normalization.

workstreams.title: Data pipeline parity (datasets/parsers/transform)
deliverables: Pure-Rust protobuf decoders for Instance/Example/ExampleBatch length-delimited streams.
Pure-Rust dataset sources: files/globs, pattern expansion, sharding, and deterministic prefetching (threaded iterator).
Pure-Rust transforms mirroring Python surfaces: instance_reweight, negative_gen, transform pipeline definitions.
parityChecks: Fixture-based decoding parity: sparse features (fids) and dense/extra fields equal after canonicalization.
Pattern expansion parity: DATE/INT ranges resolve to identical ordered lists.
Transform parity: deterministic seeds produce identical outputs and sample counts.
tests: Golden fixtures for parsing minimal Instance/Example/ExampleBatch inputs.
Golden fixtures for transform configs and outputs (JSON lines or protobuf bytes).
Property tests for pattern expansion and sharding determinism.
risks: Python relies on TF custom ops for some dataset kernels; exact semantics may require re-implementing kernels in Rust or accepting scoped parity for Candle-first path.
Kafka behaviors (timeouts, batching) differ across clients; parity must define canonical semantics (ordering + at-least-once).

reasons: Core data parsing and transformation can be implemented as pure Rust without TensorFlow runtime.

workstreams.title: Distribution/runtime parity (distributed_ps, cluster/service discovery, sync/barrier ops)
deliverables: Rust discovery implementations for TF_CONFIG and service discovery backends (ZK/Consul); deterministic ordering of endpoints.
Rust barrier coordination primitive usable by Candle-only training and by TF-bridge mode.
Rust gRPC clients for remote_predict and parameter_sync with timeouts and retry semantics modeled after Python.
parityChecks: Cluster resolution parity: for a given TF_CONFIG and discovery backend responses, Rust builds the same cluster view.
Barrier parity: block/unblock detection and timeout behavior matches test oracle.
tests: Golden tests for TF_CONFIG parsing and cluster spec normalization.
Integration tests with mock gRPC servers for prediction_service and parameter_sync.
Unit tests for barrier state machine and deterministic retry/backoff.
risks: Python runtime binds deeply to tf.estimator lifecycles; Rust must define an explicit lifecycle for Candle and optionally shim TF lifecycles behind features.
MPI/Horovod/BytePS behavior is out of scope for initial Candle-only parity; treat as optional backends with a staged rollout.

reasons: Discovery and coordination do not require TensorFlow runtime.
TF graph execution parity is gated behind tf-runtime features and separate from this workstream.

workstreams.title: Embedding hash table + optimizer config parity
deliverables: Rust builders for optimizer/initializer/compressor/table configs emitting identical protobufs to Python.
Candle-first in-memory embedding hash table backend with deterministic lookup/apply_gradients.
Optional TF custom-op bridge backend behind feature tf-custom-ops for legacy parity.
parityChecks: Proto bytes parity for a matrix of OptimizerConfig/InitializerConfig/FloatCompressorConfig cases.
Optimizer step parity: for synthetic ids/grads, updated embeddings match Python reference within defined tolerances.
tests: Golden protobuf fixtures for config messages.
Deterministic unit tests for each optimizer type (SGD/Adagrad/Adam/FTRL/Momentum/RMSProp/etc).
Integration test: tiny embedding table with a few ids, run multiple steps and compare to Python oracle outputs.
risks: Python has multiple production backends (cuckoo/multi cuckoo/gpu) implemented in C++/CUDA; full parity may require reusing those kernels or accepting Candle-only backend parity.
Stochastic rounding and fp16 transfer introduce nondeterminism unless explicitly seeded and modeled.

reasons: Config/proto parity and Candle-first embedding backend do not require TensorFlow runtime.
Bridge to TF custom ops is optional and feature-gated.

workstreams.title: Export/checkpoint parity (save_utils, dense_reload_utils, model_export/**)
deliverables: Rust reader/writer for monolith_checkpoint text proto and checkpoint directory normalization.
Rust implementation of exempt checkpoint retention logic (max_to_keep + exemptions).
TF-dependent export/import helpers behind tf-runtime to produce SavedModel-compatible outputs when required.
parityChecks: monolith_checkpoint parsing parity and normalization (relative path expansion, invalid path removal).
When tf-runtime enabled, exported SavedModel structure matches Python exporter expectations (graph names, signature names, asset placement).
tests: Golden tests for dense_reload alias mapping rules (string-based transforms) independent of TF.
Feature-gated integration test: export minimal SavedModel using TF runtime and verify layout.
risks: TF checkpoint binary formats and SavedModel writing are complex without TF runtime; initial Rust scope should focus on metadata + optional TF-enabled bridge.
dense_reload_utils uses TF checkpoint readers to fetch tensors; pure Rust parity may require an external TF tool or a third-party reader.

reasons: SavedModel export/import and TF checkpoint tensor IO require TensorFlow runtime for full parity.
This workstream is gated behind tf-runtime; default builds must not depend on vendoring TF libraries.

workstreams.title: Hooks/metrics/summary parity
deliverables: Rust hook lifecycle (before/after step, before/after checkpoint, shutdown) aligned to Candle training loop.
Metrics emission compatibility layer (counters/timers/store) with stable naming and tags.
Summary writing abstraction; TF summary behind tf-runtime feature.
parityChecks: Hook ordering constraints preserved: restore before training, save after, barrier around save where applicable.
Metric payload parity: same metric names/tags and deterministic timestamp handling (timestamps only in runtime, not in goldens).
tests: Unit tests for hook ordering in a toy training loop.
Golden tests for metric payload canonicalization (sorted tags).
risks: Python uses tf.estimator SessionRunHook; Rust must model equivalent callback timing precisely.
External sinks (Kafka/DeepInsight) must be mocked; ensure tests do not require network.

reasons: Hooks/metrics can be implemented without TensorFlow runtime; TF-specific summary writing is optional.

workstreams.title: Supporting utilities
deliverables: Rust equivalents for env detection (YARN/CLOUDNATIVE), IP utilities, file abstraction hooks used by training/predict.
Config helpers mirroring Python defaults and override precedence.
parityChecks: Environment-derived values (local host selection) match Python for the same env vars.
Config override precedence matches Python (explicit config > flags > env > defaults).
tests: Unit tests that set env vars and validate resolved host/ports.
risks: Some Python utilities rely on TF graph collections; Rust must refactor these into explicit parameters and return values.

reasons: Utility behavior is independent of TensorFlow runtime.

definitionOfDone: All Python files are mapped to Rust targets or justified N/A in the plan.
Shared fixture root exists and contains the first goldens (parse_instance_minimal, optimizer_config_proto_roundtrip, monolith_checkpoint_state_text).
monolith-data parses Instance/Example/ExampleBatch fixtures into canonical Rust structures.
Rust parity tests match Python goldens for minimal fixtures.
Implement pure-Rust transforms (instance_reweight, negative_gen, basic label utilities) with deterministic seeds.
Parity tests cover at least one representative config for each transform.
Rust emits protobuf configs identical to Python for optimizers/initializers/compressors/table config structs.
Golden protobuf byte comparisons pass.
In-memory embedding backend supports lookup/apply_gradients/assign/assign_add for a subset of optimizers with deterministic tests.
End-to-end Candle toy training loop runs using the embedding backend and produces stable checkpoints/metrics (Rust-native).
Rust parses TF_CONFIG and supports mock discovery backends for tests.
Mocked remote_predict and parameter_sync clients pass integration tests with deterministic retries/timeouts.
Rust barrier primitive passes unit tests for block/unblock semantics and timeout handling.
Candle training loop can coordinate a save barrier in a multi-worker simulation (single process test harness).
Rust reads/writes monolith_checkpoint text proto with path normalization and exemptions.
Parity tests pass for checkpoint_state fixture.
Introduce cargo features: tf-runtime and tf-custom-ops; TF-dependent modules compile only when enabled.
Default builds and tests run without TensorFlow runtime present.
With tf-runtime enabled, Rust can export a minimal SavedModel layout matching Python structure for entry and at least one subgraph.
Feature-gated smoke test validates deterministic signature names and asset placement.

openGaps.gap: Missing generated/parity/11-normalize-mapping/normalized_mapping.json; plan uses heuristic mapping only.
openGaps.mitigation: Regenerate normalized mapping and refine Rust ownership boundaries and module placement.

openGaps.gap: Many pipeline and runtime behaviors are implemented as TensorFlow custom ops (gen_monolith_ops) in C++/CUDA.
openGaps.mitigation: Stage parity: (1) Candle-first pure Rust pipeline and backends; (2) TF bridge behind features; (3) selectively port kernels to Rust where feasible.

openGaps.gap: SavedModel and TF checkpoint tensor IO parity is difficult without TF runtime.
openGaps.mitigation: Keep TF IO behind tf-runtime; for Candle-only path, define a Rust-native checkpoint format and provide separate conversion tools.
